        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 1,
          "text": "Notes About Online References",
          "style": "h1",
          "id": "sec-notes",
          "number": {
            "series": "part",
            "format": "upper-roman",
            "suffix": "."
          },
          "set_string": [
            {
              "name": "section",
              "value": "III. Notes About Online References"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "The guidelines for citing electronic information as offered here are in modified illustration of the adaptation by the International Standards Organization (ISO) documentation system and the American Psychological Association style. There are various options for including a URL in a reference. Follow the order of details and whether a period needs to be placed at the end of the reference. The style of the accessed date is “Accessed: Abbrev. month and day, year.”",
          "style": "body"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Order of details (whether a period is added at the end):",
          "style": "body"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Accessed date. [Online]. Available: URL, DOI (add period at end).",
                "style": "bullet"
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Accessed date. [Online]. Available: URL (no period at end)",
                "style": "bullet"
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Accessed date, DOI (add period at end).",
                "style": "bullet"
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "URL, DOI (add period at end).",
                "style": "bullet"
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "(no accessed date), DOI (add period at end unless hyperlink).",
                "style": "bullet"
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "URL (no period at end)",
                "style": "bullet"
              }
            ]
          ],
          "marker": "•",
          "style": "bullet"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Guidelines for Breaking URLs:",
          "style": "basic"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Break after slash or double slash.",
                "style": "bullet"
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Break “before” the hyphen that is part of an address, but do not break after; do not add hyphens or spaces; do not let addresses hyphenate.",
                "style": "bullet"
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Break “before” a tilde (~), a hyphen, an underscore (_), a question mark, or a percent (%) symbol.",
                "style": "bullet"
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Break before or after an equal sign or an ampersand (follow the same rule for the “at” (@) symbol).",
                "style": "bullet"
              }
            ]
          ],
          "marker": "•",
          "style": "bullet"
