          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Tips for abbreviating periodical titles in references: words ending in “-ology” can be ended after the “-ol.”; words ending in “-graphy” after the “-gr.”; compound words using the abbreviation of the last word. Some abbreviations apply to more than one word (e.g., “Mathematical” and “Mathematics” are both “Math.”).",
